<DocSection Title="Prerequisites">
    <p>Before you scaffold your first project, install the following on your machine:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>.NET 10 SDK</b> or later — <MudLink Href="https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download" Target="_blank">download</MudLink>.</li>
        <li><b>SQL Server</b> — LocalDB or Express is fine for development. Production apps typically run against full SQL Server or Azure SQL.</li>
        <li>An IDE: <b>Visual Studio 2022+</b>, <b>JetBrains Rider</b>, or <b>VS Code</b> with the C# Dev Kit.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>You can verify your .NET SDK version with:</p>
    <DocSnippet Name="VerifyDotnetVersion" Language="bash" />

    <DocCallout Type="DocCalloutType.Note">
        Some optional features need extra tooling. You can skip these now and add them later as needed.
    </DocCallout>

    <ul>
        <li><b>Azure Cosmos DB Emulator</b> — only if you plan to use Cosmos replication.</li>
        <li><b>Azure Functions Core Tools</b> — only if your project includes the optional Functions project.</li>
        <li><b>Azurite</b> — local emulator for Azure Storage, used by file upload features in development.</li>
    </ul>
</DocSection>

